Ubuntu / Debian quick installation:
. ./install-Elvex.sh




The full compilation of Elvex requires the following programs on your computer:

— g++
— flex (only if you need to recompile lex files)
— bison (only if you need to recompile yacc file)
— aclocal
— automake 
— autoconf
— libxml2-dev

Once you have downloaded Elvex execute these commands:

aclocal
automake −a
autoconf
./configure
make
sudo make install

. ./try-it.sh
